### ============================================================
### FASE 2 — PRODUCTOS Y WAREHOUSE
### ============================================================
### Los productos son la mercancía que se comprará al proveedor.
### El warehouse es la bodega de destino de la orden de compra.
### ============================================================

### 2.1 Crear productos del tenant
### → Guardar primer product_variant_id en @variantId
### → Guardar segundo product_variant_id en @variantId2
POST {{baseUrl}}/product
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "products": [
    {
      "tenant_id": "{{tenantId}}",
      "sku": "PROD-001",
      "variant_name": "Cuaderno universitario 100 hojas",
      "unit_price": 1500,
      "cabys_code": "44121600"
    },
    {
      "tenant_id": "{{tenantId}}",
      "sku": "PROD-002",
      "variant_name": "Lapicero azul BIC",
      "unit_price": 350,
      "cabys_code": "44121700"
    }
  ]
}

###

### 2.2 Consultar productos del tenant (verificación)
GET {{baseUrl}}/product/{{tenantId}}

###

### 2.3 Crear bodega de destino para la orden de compra
### → Guardar warehouse_id en @warehouseId
### NOTA: is_branch=false → bodega de almacenamiento general
###       Para que la bodega sea la bodega principal de la sucursal
###       se debe crear con is_branch=true (campo en BD, no en el DTO de creación)
POST {{baseUrl}}/warehouse
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "branch_id": "{{branchId}}",
  "warehouse_name": "Bodega Central",
  "warehouse_address": "San José, La Uruca, Costa Rica"
}

###

### 2.4 Consultar bodegas del tenant (verificación)
GET {{baseUrl}}/warehouse/tenant/

###

### 2.5 Verificar stock inicial (debe estar en 0 para ambos productos)
### → Confirmar que no hay stock antes de la orden de compra
POST {{baseUrl}}/warehouse/count
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "warehouse_id": "{{warehouseId}}"
}

###


### ============================================================
### FASE 3 — PROVEEDOR
### ============================================================

### 3.1 Crear proveedor
### → Guardar supplier_id en @supplierId
POST {{baseUrl}}/suppliers
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "supplier_name": "Papelería Nacional S.A.",
  "supplier_contact_info": "ventas@papnacional.cr | +506 2222-3333",
  "supplier_address": "Barrio Amón, San José, Costa Rica",
  "supplier_notes": "Proveedor principal para artículos de oficina"
}

###

### 3.2 Consultar todos los proveedores (verificación)
GET {{baseUrl}}/suppliers

###


### ============================================================
### FASE 4 — CREAR ORDEN DE COMPRA
### ============================================================
### create_purchase_order() ejecuta automáticamente:
###   - INSERT purchase_order + purchase_order_item (2 items)
###   - Calcula subtotal y tax → INSERT purchase_account_payable
###   - INSERT supplier_invoice + supplier_invoice_item (has_invoice=true)
###
### Cálculo de montos (IVA 13%):
###   Item 1: PROD-001 × 100 × 1,200 = 120,000.00
###   Item 2: PROD-002 × 200 × 250   =  50,000.00
###   ─────────────────────────────────────────────
###   subtotal = 170,000.00 CRC
###   tax (13%) =  22,100.00 CRC
###   total    = 192,100.00 CRC
###
### payment_condition: días plazo para pago (30 = 30 días)
### ============================================================

### 4.1 Crear orden de compra
### → Guardar purchase_order_id en @purchaseOrderId
### → Guardar purchase_account_payable_id en @accountPayableId
###   (viene en la respuesta o consultando GET /purchase/:id)
POST {{baseUrl}}/purchase
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "supplier_id": "{{supplierId}}",
  "warehouse_id": "{{warehouseId}}",
  "expected_delivery_date": "2026-04-15",
  "has_invoice": true,
  "payment_condition": "30",
  "items": [
    {
      "product_variant_id": "{{variantId}}",
      "quantity_ordered": 100,
      "unit_price": 1200
    },
    {
      "product_variant_id": "{{variantId2}}",
      "quantity_ordered": 200,
      "unit_price": 250
    }
  ]
}

###

### 4.2 Consultar detalle completo de la orden recién creada
### → Verificar: items, invoice, payable, status=Pending (1)
### → Copiar purchase_account_payable_id en @accountPayableId
GET {{baseUrl}}/purchase/{{purchaseOrderId}}

###

### 4.3 Consultar todas las órdenes de compra del tenant
GET {{baseUrl}}/purchase

###


### ============================================================
### FASE 5 — PAGOS
### ============================================================
### Flujo:
###   - Registrar pago → verify_purchase_order_payment() se ejecuta
###     automáticamente en BD y actualiza purchase_account_payable
###   - payment_method_id: 1=Efectivo, 2=Transferencia, 3=Tarjeta
###
### Pago 1 (parcial): 100,000.00 CRC
### Pago 2 (final):    92,100.00 CRC
### Total pagado:      192,100.00 CRC
### ============================================================

### 5.1 Registrar pago parcial (pago 1 de 2)
### → El account_payable queda en estado "Pago Parcial"
POST {{baseUrl}}/purchase/payment
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "purchase_account_payable_id": "{{accountPayableId}}",
  "amount_paid": 100000,
  "payment_method_id": 2,
  "payment_reference": "TRANSF-2026-001"
}

###

### 5.2 Consultar estado de la cuenta por pagar tras pago parcial
### → Verificar: amount_paid=100,000 / balance_remaining=92,100 / is_paid=false
GET {{baseUrl}}/purchase/{{purchaseOrderId}}

###

### 5.3 Registrar pago final (pago 2 de 2)
### → El account_payable queda en estado "Pagado" / supplier_invoice.paid=true
POST {{baseUrl}}/purchase/payment
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "purchase_account_payable_id": "{{accountPayableId}}",
  "amount_paid": 92100,
  "payment_method_id": 3,
  "payment_reference": "TC-VISA-2026-001"
}

###

### 5.4 Consultar estado de la orden tras pago completo
### → Verificar: is_paid=true / balance_remaining=0 / invoice pagada
GET {{baseUrl}}/purchase/{{purchaseOrderId}}

###


### ============================================================
### FASE 6 — TRANSICIONES DE ESTADO
### ============================================================
### Máquina de estados:
###   1 (Pending) → 2 (Shipped) → 3 (Delivered) → terminal
###
### Al llegar a Delivered (3):
###   DB Trigger: create_goods_receipt()
###     → INSERT goods_receipt (subtotal y tax desde purchase_account_payable)
###     → INSERT goods_receipt_item x2 (copia quantity_ordered de cada PO item)
###     → CALL execute_three_way_matching(purchase_order_id, goods_receipt_id)
###        → Compara subtotales, tax, totales, y cantidades
###        → INSERT three_way_matching (amounts_matched, quantities_matched, is_matched)
###
###   PurchaseService.updateOrderStatus():
###     → Llama receiveStockFromPurchase() por cada item del PO
###        → UPSERT inventory (stock += quantity_ordered)
###        → INSERT inventory_log (type_id=1=IN)
### ============================================================

### 6.1 Transición: Pending (1) → Shipped (2)
### → El pedido fue despachado por el proveedor / en tránsito
### → No genera goods_receipt ni actualiza inventario
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/purchase/{{purchaseOrderId}}/status
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status_id": 2
}

###

### 6.2 Verificar estado Shipped
### → purchase_order_status_id debe ser 2
GET {{baseUrl}}/purchase/{{purchaseOrderId}}

###

### 6.3 Transición: Shipped (2) → Delivered (3)
### ⚡ Este request dispara automáticamente:
###    - DB trigger: goods_receipt + three_way_matching
###    - PurchaseService: inventory update por cada item
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/purchase/{{purchaseOrderId}}/status
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status_id": 3
}

###


### ============================================================
### FASE 7 — VERIFICACIÓN: THREE-WAY MATCHING + INVENTARIO
### ============================================================

### 7.1 Consultar resultado del three-way matching
### → Esperar: amounts_matched=true, quantities_matched=true, is_matched=true
### → Revisar amount_comparison y quantity_comparison para detalles
GET {{baseUrl}}/purchase/{{purchaseOrderId}}/matching

###

### 7.2 Consultar orden completa (estado final)
### → Verificar: status=Delivered (3), pagos completos, invoice pagada
GET {{baseUrl}}/purchase/{{purchaseOrderId}}

###

### 7.3 Verificar stock en bodega tras Delivered
### → Esperar:
###    - PROD-001 (Cuaderno):   stock = 100 unidades
###    - PROD-002 (Lapicero):   stock = 200 unidades
POST {{baseUrl}}/warehouse/count
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "warehouse_id": "{{warehouseId}}"
}

###

### 7.4 Consultar log de movimientos de inventario
### → Esperar 2 entradas tipo IN:
###    - product_variant_id=@variantId  / quantity=100
###    - product_variant_id=@variantId2 / quantity=200
GET {{baseUrl}}/warehouse/{{warehouseId}}/log

###


### ============================================================
### VERIFICACIONES ADICIONALES
### ============================================================

### V1. Intentar transición inválida desde Delivered (debe fallar 400)
### → Transicion invalida: 3 -> 2
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/purchase/{{purchaseOrderId}}/status
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status_id": 2
}

###

### V2. Forzar three-way matching manualmente (idempotente)
### → Debe devolver el mismo resultado sin duplicar el registro
POST {{baseUrl}}/purchase/twm
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "purchase_order_id": "{{purchaseOrderId}}"
}

###

### V3. Consultar todas las órdenes (estado final del tenant)
GET {{baseUrl}}/purchase

###

### V4. Consultar bodegas del tenant (estado final)
GET {{baseUrl}}/warehouse/tenant/

###
